The paper deals with image restoration using denoising autoencoder networks as priors. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) domain. The paper also involves optimization using gradient descent and backpropagation, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). Additionally, the paper involves information theory concepts such as negative log likelihood, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) domain. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.IT.
